data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your manual expression tree won't compile. Replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more `Expression.Lambda`, `Expression.Call`, etc. The parameter is now a regular lambda, so conditionals work naturally.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

**Flat:** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously silently shared one `Street` column. EF 10 appends a number (e.g. `Street`, `Street1`). This will generate a migration that **renames columns** and breaks existing data.

**Nested:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was column `BillingAddress_City`, now becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

Fix both by pinning column names explicitly:

```csharp
// Flat — pin shared names
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// Nested — preserve old column name
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

After updating, run `dotnet ef migrations add UpgradeEF10` and inspect — there should be **no** column rename operations if you pinned correctly.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter for redacted SQL logging. Add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update all other methods on the interface similarly (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
